{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix Memory Leak in Logical Channel Configuration Cleanup\n\n### Summary\nWhile investigating a socket resource leak reported downstream of `set_default_logicalchannelconfig()` in `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_UE/config_ue.c`, a more fundamental memory leak was discovered in the logical channel management code. The function `configure_logicalChannelBearer()` was calling `asn_sequence_del()` to remove entries from `mac->lc_ordered_list` without first freeing the `nr_lcordered_info_t` structures allocated by `calloc()`. This resulted in unrecoverable memory growth during RRC reconfigurations that modified logical channel configurations.\n\nAdditionally, a similar leak was found in `release_mac_configuration()` in `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_UE/main_ue_nr.c` where all logical channels were being cleared without proper memory deallocation.\n\nAlthough the original socket leak report could not be directly reproduced, these memory leaks represent critical resource management failures that could manifest as system instability or resource exhaustion under load. The fix ensures all dynamically allocated `nr_lcordered_info_t` entries are properly freed before sequence removal.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_UE/config_ue.c`: Added `free(mac->lc_ordered_list.array[j])` before `asn_sequence_del()` when releasing individual logical channels in `configure_logicalChannelBearer()`.\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_UE/main_ue_nr.c`: Added `free(mac->lc_ordered_list.array[i - 1])` before `asn_sequence_del()` when clearing all logical channels in `release_mac_configuration()`.\n\n"
}